
[1]insolation

   INSOLA'TION, n. The act of exposing to the rays of the sun for drying
   or maturing, as fruits, drugs, &c. or for rendering acid, as vinegar,
   or for promoting some chimical action of one substance on another.

   1. A stroke of the sun; the action of extreme heat on the brain.
